SQL_STMT_U.val:
SELECT a.CLNT101_ADMNO, a.CLNT102_CLNTNO, a.CLNT110_NAME1, cast (sum (b.CMON_TOTSALDEBTNOTESMAN + b.CMON_TOTSALDEBTNOTESAUTO) as decimal (13,2)), cast (sum (b.CMON_TOTCOMMISSIONINCOME) as decimal (13,2)), cast (sum (b.CMON_TOTINTERESTINCOME) as decimal (13,2)), cast (sum (b.CMON_TOTOTHERINCOME) as decimal (13,2)), cast (sum (b.CMON_CURRBALINVESTMENT) :5 as decimal (13,2))
FROM :1/CLNT a :3 left join :1/CMON b on b.CMON_ADMNO = a.CLNT101_ADMNO and b.CMON_CLNTNO = a.CLNT102_CLNTNO and b.CMON_CLNTNO <> 99999 and b.CMON_CURRENCY = ':6' :4
where :2
group by a.CLNT101_ADMNO, a.CLNT102_CLNTNO, a.CLNT110_NAME1
order by a.CLNT101_ADMNO, a.CLNT102_CLNTNO
for fetch only with UR optimize for 100 rows

Text.val: -- If Year / Month = "ytd amounts" was selected then the sum of
-- CMON_CURRBALINVESTMENT has to be calculated different

SQL_STMT_U.val: SELECT a.CLNT101_ADMNO, a.CLNT102_CLNTNO FROM :1/CLNT a :3, :1/CMON b where :2 :4 and b.CMON_ADMNO = a.CLNT101_ADMNO and b.CMON_CLNTNO = a.CLNT102_CLNTNO and b.CMON_CURRENCY = ':5' for fetch only with UR

SELECT cast (sum (b.CMON_CURRBALINVESTMENT) / max(sum(abs(sign(b.CMON_CURRBALINVESTMENT))),1) as decimal (13,2)) FROM :1/CLNT a :3, :1/CMON b where :2 :4 and b.CMON_ADMNO = a.CLNT101_ADMNO and b.CMON_CLNTNO = a.CLNT102_CLNTNO and b.CMON_CLNTNO <> 99999 and b.CMON_CURRENCY = ':5' group by a.CLNT101_ADMNO, a.CLNT102_CLNTNO, a.CLNT110_NAME1 order by a.CLNT101_ADMNO, a.CLNT102_CLNTNO for fetch only with UR optimize for 100 rows
